title Note Created

Browser->Server: HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note
Server --> Browser : Redirect Location
note over Browser: 
The browser goes to the redirects 
location sent
end note
Browser->Server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/ampleapp/notes
note over Browser: 
The browser start the same process
of loading the page
end note
Server --> Browser : HTML Code

Browser->Server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
Server-->Browser: CSS Code (main.css)
Browser->Server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
Server-->Browser: JS Code (main.js)

Browser->Server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
Server-->Browser: [{ content: "message sent", date: "note creation date" }, ...]

note over Browser: 
The browser renders the new generated note
(included old notes)
end note



---------------------------------------------------------


title New Note Spa

note over Browser: 
The browser add the new note and render it.
end note
Browser->Server: HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa { content :  "new note" , date : "2020-05-13"}

Server --> Browser : Response {message: "note created"}

note over Browser: 
The browser send the new generated note
to the server without redirect (only save the new note)
end note

 

